messages.content: is this the right tutorial ?

i think so yep. here's what i ran when i installed my subtensor: 

cd root directory

`git clone https://github.com/opentensor/subtensor.git`

`sudo ufw allow 30333/tcp`

`cd subtensor/`

`sudo ./scripts/run/subtensor.sh -e docker --network mainnet --node-type lite`

then confirm local subtensor is running with:

`btcli s list --subtensor.chain_endpoint ws://127.0.0.1:9944` - you should see a list of subnets

finally i ran `docker ps` to see if subtensor was running
